snippet: After the worst mass shooting in American history, Congress is showing little sign of rallying around bipartisan legislation in a bitter election year.
abstract: News Analysis; election-year politics and number of hotly contested Senate races will likely continue to contribute to blocking of meaningful gun control legislation by United States Congress, despite renewed urgency following Orlando, Fla, shooting.

byline.contributor: Julie Hirschfeld Davis contributed reporting from Orlando, Fla.

lead_paragraph: After the worst mass shooting in American history, Congress is showing little sign of rallying around bipartisan legislation in a bitter election year.

headline.print_headline: Why the Shooting Is Unlikely to Inspire Major New Gun Laws
headline.main: Why the Orlando Shooting Is Unlikely to Lead to Major New Gun Laws
